[SN]TITLE[SN]
Police raids in Wrexham following Asian gold burglaries

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have arrested nine people in dawn raids in north Wales in connection with the theft of gold jewellery.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The arrests in Wrexham, Flintshire and Cheshire come after Asian gold was targeted in a spate of burglaries over the past five months.
Officers from North Wales Police and Cheshire Constabulary were involved in the operation.
Police raided and searched 18 addresses.
